EmailTemplate.subject: St Andrew's Cathedral School
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
It was lovely to speak with you today regarding our Gawura campus for Indigenous students.
As discussed, Gawura was established in 2007 and takes four students into Kindergarten each year, usually two boys and two girls. The students are on full scholarships that stay with them right throughout their schooling to Year 12.
Ive attached some information and links to provide further information.
If you have any further queries, please contact me directly on 9286 9552.
Thanks and regards
Robyn
